Yes thats right, You need premium users to watch your content. We found that premium revenue had a strong correlation with minutes watched whilst also factoring in audience value (niche, demograhics) as well as being more exploit resistant

Another big change is that we cap the premium revenue by comparing to revenue from 30 to 60 days ago.

If the **7 day average** of premium revenue for a video is more than the **median daily premium revenue** of the chennel from the lookback period the 7 day average is capped proportionally.

We found that exploitative miners cannot maintain revenue for more than a 30 day period so this capping excludes them from earning whilst very rarely affecting any genuine creators.

Check out the code for this in: `bitcast/validator/platforms/youtube/evaluation/median_capping.py`

Subnet total mining emission: $1000

Miner A weight: 0.1

Subnet total mining emission: $2000
Miner A daily emission: $100
Miner A weight: 0.05

Hey! The alpha must be staked against your mining hotkey (from any Coldkey).

Best way to do this without having to regen your chrome extension wallet elsewhere is probably to use [polkadot.js](https://polkadot.js.org/apps/?rpc=wss%3A%2F%2Fentrypoint-finney.opentensor.ai%3A443#/extrinsics) to execute a stake move.

```
Connect your chrome wallet

Extrinsic: subtensorModule.moveStake 

originHotkey: the hotkey of the validator you are currently staked to
destinationHotkey: the hotkey of your miner
originNetuid: 93
destinationNetuid: 93
alphaAmount: 1,000,000,000,000 (1000 alpha)
```

Same operation can also be done on cli but will require you to regen your wallet onto a linux machine. Read more here: https://docs.learnbittensor.org/btcli#btcli-stake-move

DM me if this is unclear and I can walk you through it
